body:
@arina-ielchiieva I've made updates based on the review. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4335237/38391975-c2e2dc08-38da-11e8-814e-fc974143afaf.png)

I've also skipped adding re-adding the Glyphicons package because we already have that as part of DRILL-6279 (PR #1197 ).

@parthchandra , @vrozov 

I have done the following modifications:
- Renamed newly added files with the prefix "VL" with "VarLen" as suggested by @parthchandra 
- After talking offline with @vrozov about his objections to the MemoryUtils and also from previous feedbacks from @parthchandra , I have a) deleted this utility, b) exposed the needed functionality under the class DrillBuf (using Netty API's), and c) used the same configuration to control the checks.

@parthchandra , @vrozov, please review this [document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BSNem_ItP-Vxlr6auSP_iwwOLM9rwWZYxGwCsXi-IE8/edit?usp=sharing) and the associated JMH code [here](https://github.com/sachouche/drill-jmh). This should provide you with performance benchmarks regarding the bulk approach that I have used in this PR request (please focus on test-3 which is Parquet specific); I will be adding more fine-grained tests with regard to the Memory Access tests (requested by @vrozov).
